FBIS4-39906 "drsov113_a_94017" FBIS-SOV-94-113 Daily Report 11 Jun 1994 RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS Duma Committee Expresses Concern Over U.S. House Resolution Duma Committee Expresses Concern Over U.S. House Resolution LD1106225294 Moscow Mayak Radio Network in Russian 2200 GMT 11 Jun 94 LD1106225294 Moscow Mayak Radio Network Russian BFN [Text] The committee for international affairs of the Russian State Duma has expressed concern over the adoption by the House of Representatives of the U.S. Congress of a resolution in favor of the unilateral lifting of embargo on arms supplies to Bosnian Muslims. The statement adopted by the lower chamber of the Russian parliament notes that such a measure would lead to an escalation of conflict in southern Yugoslavia [as heard] and undermine the current peace process. In this situation the committee sees it as its obligation to reaffirm a recommendation to the president and the government of the Russian Federation to study the question of taking practical measures to lift unjustified sanctions imposed on the Federal Republic of Yugoslavia.
